  "text": "Ultrasound diagnosis of placenta accreta is suspected when there is at least one of the following signs: placental lacunae, obliteration of the retroplacental clear space, interruption of bladder boundaries, andmyometrial thickness less than 1 mm [CITATION_1] . In our case there was only the first sign and it was interpreted as a subchorionic hematoma.",
